name: Central Park
overview: An animated musical comedy about the Tillermans, a family that lives in a castle in Central Park. Owen, the park manager, and Paige, his journalist wife, raise their kids Molly and Cole in the world’s most famous park, while fending off a hotel heiress, Bitsy Brandenham, who would love nothing more than to turn the park into condos.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: In season two, Molly experiences the trials and tribulations of adolescence, Cole is challenged by a truly embarrassing moment at school, Paige continues to chase down the mayor’s corruption story and Owen juggles managing the park, his staff and his family all with a smile on his face. Meanwhile, Bitsy inches ever closer to her sinister goal of claiming Central Park as her own, with Helen by her side eternally wondering whether she’s made it into Bitsy’s will.

seasons.name: Season 3
seasons.overview: In season three, as Bitsy continues her relentless pursuit to buy the park, Owen embarks on a new promotional campaign to make more people fall in love with it, and Paige finds herself busier than ever when she lands her first book deal.

tagline: A musical walk in the park.

episodes.name: Episode One
episodes.overview: An event goes awry in the New York park, which Owen manages and lives in with his family. Paige chases a hard news story.

episodes.name: Skater’s Circle
episodes.overview: Bitsy pitches her plan to buy the park. Owen deals with a mini-mugging in Skater’s Circle.

episodes.name: Hat Luncheon
episodes.overview: Owen speaks at a tense Hat Luncheon charity event. Cole helps Molly meet up with Brendan.

episodes.name: Garbage Ballet
episodes.overview: Paige hunts a rat, Owen battles trash in the park, and Molly obsesses over her disastrous first kiss.

episodes.name: Dog Spray Afternoon
episodes.overview: Owen grapples with a graffiti artist tagging the park, while Helen plots against Bitsy’s dog, Shampagne.

episodes.name: Rival Busker
episodes.overview: Birdieʼs job is threatened by a rival busker, Bitsy hosts a wedding, and Paige spends the night at The Brandenham.

episodes.name: Squirrel, Interrupted
episodes.overview: Cole and Owen do a scavenger hunt in Central Park. Paige discovers Molly is a great chess player.

episodes.name: Hot Oven
episodes.overview: Molly introduces Brendan to the family. Helen stumbles upon a new way to get Shampagne out of her life.

episodes.name: Live it Up Tonight
episodes.overview: Molly and Cole go on a special park tour as Owen and Paige try to have a date night.

episodes.name: A Fish Called Snakehead
episodes.overview: Season finale. Owen and his family search for a snakehead fish that might be in the Harlem Meer. Bitsy works with a likability consultant.

episodes.name: Central Dark
episodes.overview: A tristate blackout leaves Bitsy and Helen trapped in New Jersey—and forces the Tillerman family to see each other in a new light.

episodes.name: Mother's Daze
episodes.overview: Owen and the kids go all out for Paige on Mother’s Day. Bitsy has to handle things on her own when Helen takes a day off.

episodes.name: Fista Puffs Mets Out Justice
episodes.overview: As a test to see if she's worthy of joining an elite girl group, Fista Puffs battles a monster in the Metropolitan Museum of Art.

episodes.name: Of Course You Realize This Means Ward
episodes.overview: Owen oversees a kids' field trip in the park, while Molly and Cole help Brendan with his indoor kite competition. Bitsy and her brother write memoirs.

episodes.name: Down to the Underwire
episodes.overview: When Molly needs a new bra, Owen takes her shopping. Helen finds a key that could finally reveal whether she's in Bitsy’s will.

episodes.name: The Shadow
episodes.overview: The Brandenham is robbed by a jewel thief, reminding Bitsy of a criminal who terrorized the hotel over 50 years ago.

episodes.name: A Decent Proposal
episodes.overview: Owen does damage control after accidentally ruining a marriage proposal. Molly attends Bitsy’s birthday party with Brendan.

episodes.name: Sir Bricks-A-Lot
episodes.overview: When Owen considers a new job in Connecticut, the family uses Cole’s toys to imagine what their lives would be like if they moved out of the park.

episodes.name: A Boat-iful Mind
episodes.overview: Cole finds an escape from his homework in model sail-boating. Molly becomes a published artist in the school newspaper but isn’t proud of her work.

episodes.name: Bee Is for Brandenham
episodes.overview: Owen is called to the Brandenham to help Bitsy deal with a swarm of bees, while Paige and the kids attempt to care for her boss’ cat.

episodes.name: The PAIGE-riarchy!
episodes.overview: Paige tries to convince Molly that her period is a blessing. Bitsy is desperate to get back on a prestigious list of rich women over 50.

episodes.name: Castle Sweet Castle
episodes.overview: Owen and Paige set out to make the castle everything they dreamed it would be—if they can get the approval.

episodes.name: Celeste We Forget
episodes.overview: Owen’s mom derails a trip to the botanical garden when she makes a surprise visit. Paige chases a lead while writing a fluff piece on gifting suites.

episodes.name: The Ballad of Johnnie Lee
episodes.overview: After an embarrassing moment at school, Cole wants to change his name and identity. Owen, Paige, and Molly tell stories to help him cope.

episodes.name: Where There’s Smoke
episodes.overview: In search of evidence for a story, Paige brings the family to a wake. Bitsy and Helen try to convince a big investor to join them in buying Central Park.

episodes.name: The Lyin’ in Winter
episodes.overview: Bitsy and Helen get stranded during a blizzard. The family finds out that the deal to sell Central Park is happening today. Season finale.

episodes.name: A Star Is Owen
episodes.overview: The Tillerman family welcomes spring as an episode of a hit crime show films in the park.

episodes.name: Paige’s Next Chapter
episodes.overview: As Paige prepares for a big meeting with a book publisher, she welcomes her sister Abby to New York City.

episodes.name: Ice Ice Not Baby
episodes.overview: Molly and Brendan get into their first big fight, while Abby gets her first big commercial audition for a local deli.

episodes.name: A Triptych Down Memory Lane
episodes.overview: Elwood forgets the password he created for the Tillermans’ hard drive, so the family must help him remember it or their memories will be erased.

episodes.name: Golden Owen: Manager Damager
episodes.overview: In order to get his “I Heart the Park” campaign proposal approved, Owen has to repair old friendships at the Park Managers’ Conference.

episodes.name: A Matter of Life and Boeuf
episodes.overview: When the Tillermans visit Abby at her new job as waitress, a precious item goes missing—and everyone in the restaurant is a suspect.

episodes.name: Slumber-Dog-Molly-An-Aire
episodes.overview: Molly hosts her first teenage slumber party, which creates a rift between her and Paige.

episodes.name: Lunar Palaver
episodes.overview: On the day of the Lunar Palaver—a big Squirrel Quarrels event—Cole has a run-in with a racist lady in the park.

episodes.name: A Killer Deadline
episodes.overview: Paige checks into a hotel to focus on two writing deadlines. Owen volunteers for a school kickball tournament that Molly is trying to avoid.

episodes.name: Money Candy
episodes.overview: Owen and Paige set out to buy tickets to a K-pop boy band’s concert for the kids. Bitsy looks into cloning her dog.

episodes.name: The Puffs Go Poof
episodes.overview: Fista Puffs considers straightening her hair.

episodes.name: A Hot Dog to Remember
episodes.overview: When a beloved hot dog vendor has to take a rare morning off, Owen and Cole volunteer to help set up his cart so he can break a park record.

episodes.name: The Brandenpire Strikes Back
episodes.overview: Owen’s “I Heart the Park” campaign is in full swing with all hands on deck. Bitsy schemes to cement her political influence. Season finale.
